main event: A dull grey object was observed passing between the stars Regulus and Uranus for 10-15 seconds on April 10, 1964 between 8:15 PM and 9:15 PM.
interesting points: The object was observed by an unspecified source and forwarded to the Air Force's Intelligence Division.
The sighting was reported to the Director of Collection at A2S/Intelligence, Colonel George W. Lundquist.
The report indicates the object passed to the left of Regulus and to the right of Uranus.
The sighting occurred during a time with no moonlight.
The report mentions the location was not reported.
